    (why "bound names, one- and two-argument known calls, record-backed self field read/write, named class method dispatch, default class-instance records, arity-aware dispatch, arity-selected compiled overload calls, template/generic metadata, and effect-once let bindings give method bodies a real class-image floor; target assembly receipts and native metal/emit rows keep the metal-plane claim honest; Form-native Mach-O and ELF object wrappers prove the first per-target object floors without clang as compiler or assembler, and form-elf-exec now proves the Android ELF executable shape with _start write+exit bytes without clang, assembler, or linker; Docker Linux/arm64 and an authorized Android adb arm64 device now execute that image and verify stdout FORM ELF, empty stderr, and exit 42; Form-native JIT rows, the lowered residual cluster, the Value-ABI float/vector/string-name/JIT-offer span, numeric conversion/transcendental rows, tensor quantization, and the tensor emitter recipe now run through the fourth arm so Android is not coupled to a clang runtime dependency; a clang-like compiler binary may ship inside the Android APK as an optional oracle/accelerator, but the minimum supported Android JIT floor is the Form-native lowered recipe/table path; oracle-learning choice samples let native recipes earn runtime selection without losing the third-party teacher; full constructor syntax, generic specialization, type/generic overload selection, and fourth-arm mutable-record admission remain named cells rather than being folded into the floor prematurely")))
